Nextcloud is a safe home for all your data - community-driven, free & open
source.  Nextcloud gives you access to all your files wherever you are.

Optional dependencies:
* php-pgsql for PostgreSQL support (requires postgresql)
* php-apcu, php-memcached, or php-redis for enhanced server performance
* php-imagick for preview generation
* ffmpeg for preview generation
* libreoffice for preview generation


SlackBuild defaults

This SlackBuild uses the following defaults:
* DOCROOT=/srv/httpd/htdocs
* NCNAME=nextcloud
* PHPUSER=apache
* PHPGROUP=apache

You can change the defaults at build time:
# DOCROOT=/your/preferred/directory \
  NCNAME=nextcloud.example.com \
  PHPUSER=youruser \
  PHPGROUP=yourgroup \
  ./nextcloud-server.SlackBuild


Configuration

(1) Add the following in /etc/httpd/httpd.conf

  Alias /nextcloud "/srv/httpd/htdocs/nextcloud/"
  <Directory "/srv/httpd/htdocs/nextcloud">
      Options +FollowSymlinks
      AllowOverride All
      <IfModule mod_dav.c>
        Dav off
      </IfModule>
      SetEnv HOME      "/srv/httpd/htdocs/nextcloud"
      SetEnv HTTP_HOME "/srv/httpd/htdocs/nextcloud"
  </Directory>

(2) Enable required apache modules in /etc/httpd/httpd.conf:
    * mod_rewrite
    * mod_php or mod_fcgi and mod_setenvif

(3) (Optional) Enable recommended apache modules in /etc/httpd/httpd.conf:
    * mod_headers
    * mod_env
    * mod_dir
    * mod_mime

(4) If using authentication in a parent directory (e.g. "AuthType
    Basic"), then add "Satisfy Any" to the <Directory> entry in the
    configuration in (1).
    
(5) Restart apache

(6) You need to complete setup by visiting this page:

  http://localhost/nextcloud/
